s_tax_tab <- s_abund %>%
  dplyr::rename("taxonomy" = "clade_name") %>%
  dplyr::select(taxonomy) %>%
  tidyr::separate(taxonomy, into = c("Kingdom", "Phylum", "Class", "Order", "Family", "Genus", "Species"), sep = "\\|") %>%
  dplyr::mutate(spec_row = Species) %>%
  tibble::column_to_rownames(var = "spec_row")

Seperate OTU abudance

s_otu_tab <- s_abund %>%
  dplyr::rename("taxonomy" = "clade_name") %>%
  tidyr::separate(taxonomy, into = c("Kingdom", "Phylum", "Class", "Order", "Family", "Genus", "Species"), sep = "\\|") %>%
  dplyr::select(-clade_taxid,-Kingdom, -Phylum, -Class, -Order, -Family, -Genus) %>%
  tibble::column_to_rownames(var = "Species")
#head(s_otu_tab,5,5)

transform <- microbiome::transform
# Merge rare taxa to speed up examples
pseq <- transform(ps_mpa3_species, "compositional")
pseq <- aggregate_rare(pseq, level = "Phylum", detection = 0.00001/100, prevalence = 10/100)
pseq2<-pseq
p4 <- plot_composition(pseq2,
                       taxonomic.level = "Phylum",
                       sample.sort = "HFStatus", group_by="HFStatus",
                       x.label = "HFStatus") +
  guides(fill = guide_legend(ncol = 1)) +   scale_fill_brewer("Phylum", palette = "Paired") +
  scale_y_percent() +
  labs(x = "Samples", y = "Relative abundance (%)",
       title = "Relative abundance of taxonomic phylum")+
       #subtitle = "in derivation cohort",

Betadiversity

set.seed(1)

# Calculate bray curtis distance matrix
GH_bray <- phyloseq::distance(ps_mpa3_species, method = "bray")
# make a data frame from the sample_data
sampledf <- data.frame(sample_data(ps_mpa3_species))
# Adonis test
summary(adonis(GH_bray ~ HFStatus, data = sampledf))
## 'adonis' will be deprecated: use 'adonis2' instead
##              Length Class  Mode   
## aov.tab        6    anova  list   
## call           3    -none- call   
## coefficients   0    -none- NULL   
## coef.sites   468    -none- numeric
## f.perms      999    -none- numeric
## model.matrix 468    -none- numeric
## terms          3    terms  call
# Homogeneity of dispersion test
beta <- betadisper(GH_bray, sampledf$HFStatus)
permutest(beta)
## 
## Permutation test for homogeneity of multivariate dispersions
## Permutation: free
## Number of permutations: 999
## 
## Response: Distances
##            Df  Sum Sq  Mean Sq      F N.Perm Pr(>F)   
## Groups      1 0.05148 0.051481 6.3856    999  0.007 **
## Residuals 232 1.87037 0.008062                        
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## Betadiv


ordu.bray <- ordinate(ps_mpa3_species, "NMDS", "bray")


nmds.bray <- plot_ordination(ps_mpa3_species, ordu.bray, color="HFStatus")+ 
                 # fill.colors = c(Control="cyan4", HeartFailure="deeppink4")+
                  stat_ellipse(aes(group = HFStatus), linetype = 2)
nmds.bray <- nmds.bray + ggtitle("Bray Curtis distance") + geom_point(size = 2.5)
#+scale_fill_manual( values = c(Control="cyan4", HeartFailure="deeppink4"))

nmds.bray <- nmds.bray + theme_classic() + scale_colour_manual(values = c("cyan4", "deeppink4"))+
  annotate("text", x=0.9, y=-0.6, label= "adonis test P-value 0.001")+
  annotate("text", x=0.9, y=-0.7, label= "(adjusted age, gender and BMI)")
  #scale_color_brewer("HFStatus", palette = "Set1")
print(nmds.bray)

ggsave("HF234_betadiv_nmds_HFStatNOR2023.jpg",bg="white", width=8, height=6)
